name: Bellsprout
flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Weepinbell
flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokemon Burned and Poisoned.

name: Victreebel
flavorText: Once ingested into this Pokemon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Cacnea
flavorText: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

name: Cacturne
flavorText: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Darkness Energy attached, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Kricketune V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 3 cards in your hand. If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may draw cards until you have 4 cards in your hand instead. You can't use more than 1 Exciting Stage Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Cherubi
flavorText: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

name: Cherrim
flavorText: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokemon to it.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Rule Box (Pokemon V, Pokemon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes).

name: Carnivine
flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

name: Durant
flavorText: With their large mandibles, these Pokemon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.
Attack2Text: For each of your Durant in play, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Scatterbug
flavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Spewpa
flavorText: The beaks of birds can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.
Attack1Text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Vivillon
flavorText: The patterns on this Pokemon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.
Attack1Text: Heal all damage from 2 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Fomantis
flavorText: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Lurantis
flavorText: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it's dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Tapu Bulu
flavorText: Although it's called a guardian deity, it's violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: You may discard all Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Blipbug
flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokemon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

name: Flapple V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's attacks cost ColorlessColorless more.

name: Flapple VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Entei
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.
Attack1Text: You may attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Victini V
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Victini VMAX
Attack1Text: Attach up to 3 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Tepig
flavorText: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

name: Pignite
flavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: Emboar
flavorText: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.
Ability1Text: Your Single Strike Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Heatmor
flavorText: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Salandit
flavorText: This sneaky Pokemon will slink behind its prey and immobilize it with poisonous gas before the prey even realizes Salandit is there.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Salazzle
flavorText: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack does 90 damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Sizzlipede
flavorText: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they're well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Centiskorch
flavorText: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokemon also has large and very sharp fangs.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent flips a coin for their Burned Pokemon during Pokemon Checkup, it doesn't recover from that Special Condition even if the result is heads.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Horsea
flavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if the Defending Pokemon tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Seadra
flavorText: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.

name: Kingdra
flavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.
Ability1Text: When your Active Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, you may move any amount of Water Energy from that Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Galarian Mr. Mime
flavorText: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It'll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Galarian Mr. Rime
flavorText: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.
Attack1Text: Discard any number of Item cards that have the word "Ball" in their name from your hand. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Remoraid
flavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery
flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Rapid Strike card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You can't use more than 1 Rapid Strike Search Ability each turn.

name: Corphish
flavorText: It was originally a Pokemon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Crawdaunt
flavorText: A brutish Pokemon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.
Attack1Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Empoleon V
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Basic Pokemon in play have no Abilities, except for Pokemon with a Rule Box (Pokemon V, Pokemon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes).
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Frillish
flavorText: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon and heal all damage from it.

name: Jellicent
flavorText: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage for each Water Energy card in your discard pile.

name: Bruxish
flavorText: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie's spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: While it's often blamed for power outages, the truth is the cause of outages is more often an error on the part of the electric company.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Haymaker.

name: Electivire
flavorText: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Lightning Slam.

name: Shinx
flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: Luxio
flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Luxray
flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Pachirisu
flavorText: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Tapu Koko V
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Tapu Koko VMAX
Attack1Text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, their Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Yamper
flavorText: This gluttonous Pokemon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may put a Poke Ball card, a Great Ball card, or 1 of each from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Boltund
flavorText: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any damage counters on it, this attack can be used for Lightning.

name: Galarian Slowpoke
flavorText: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon.

name: Spoink
flavorText: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

name: Grumpig
flavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Baltoy
flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself.

name: Claydol
flavorText: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.
Attack1Text: Attach Psychic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokemon in any way you like until your Pokemon and your opponent's Pokemon have the same total amount of Energy attached.

name: Chimecho
flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Espurr
flavorText: There's enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can't be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Meowstic
flavorText: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It's when they're protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokemon to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Mimikyu V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may prevent all damage done to this Mimikyu V by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon until the end of your opponent's next turn.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon for each Prize card your opponent has taken.

name: Necrozma V
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Dottler
flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

name: Orbeetle
flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.
Attack1Text: For each Energy attached to this Pokemon, search your deck for a Stage 2 Pokemon, except Orbeetle, and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Mankey
flavorText: If one gets angry, all the others around it will get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop of Mankey.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Primeape
flavorText: The blood vessels in its brain are sturdier than those of other Pokemon, so it can stay healthy despite its constant raging.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Benched Pokemon that has any damage counters on it.

name: Onix
flavorText: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself.

name: Cubone
flavorText: It wears its mother's skull on its head, so no one knows what its bare face looks like. However, it's clear that it's always crying.

name: Marowak
flavorText: They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

name: Gligar
flavorText: It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

name: Gliscor
flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey… Then its elongated fangs do the rest.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Timburr
flavorText: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.

name: Gurdurr
flavorText: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there's skill in the way this Pokemon wields its metal beam.

name: Conkeldurr
flavorText: When going all out, this Pokemon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you're in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused. Shuffle this Pokemon and all attached cards into your deck.

name: Rolycoly
flavorText: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Carkol
flavorText: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Coalossal
flavorText: While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself.

name: Silicobra
flavorText: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

name: Sandaconda
flavorText: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 6 cards of your deck. This attack does 60 damage for each Fighting Energy card you discarded in this way.

name: Falinks
flavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokemon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Rapid Strike Pokemon in play.

name: Stonjourner
flavorText: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.
Attack1Text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Giga Hammer.

name: Single Strike Urshifu V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Fighting Energy cards and attach them to this Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Impact Blow.

name: Single Strike Urshifu VMAX
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Rapid Strike Urshifu V
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Rapid Strike Urshifu VMAX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 120 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 120 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zubat
flavorText: Their skin is so thin that they'll be burned if sunlight hits them. When it gets cold out, they gather together to warm one another's bodies.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Golbat
flavorText: They can suck down over 10 ounces of blood in one go. They have been known to drink so much blood that they can no longer fly.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Crobat
flavorText: It feeds on the blood of living people and Pokemon. If it can't drink any blood for even a short while, it becomes weak and unable to fly.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.

name: Galarian Slowbro
flavorText: If this Pokemon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.
Attack1Text: Both Active Pokemon are now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow's presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.
Attack1Text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Honchkrow
flavorText: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon can't be Asleep.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Houndour
flavorText: They make repeated eerie howls before dawn to call attention to their pack.

name: Houndoom
flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Single Strike Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Single Strike Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck. If you attached Energy to a Pokemon in this way, put 2 damage counters on that Pokemon.

name: Tyranitar V
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 4 cards of your deck.

name: Morpeko
flavorText: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.
Attack1Text: Put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: If you have no cards in your hand, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Steelix
flavorText: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Mawile
flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth, according to common lore. Be that as it may, Bronzor hates being polished.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: Many scientists suspect that this Pokemon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Metal Energy from 1 of your Pokemon to another of your Pokemon.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: A pack of these Pokemon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Slash attack does 70 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bisharp
flavorText: Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Metal Pokemon, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Honedge
flavorText: The blue eye on the sword's handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people's lives away.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Doublade
flavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Aegislash
flavorText: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokemon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch this Pokemon with an Aegislash in your hand. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Metal Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Aegislash
flavorText: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokemon to build a kingdom to its liking.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch this Pokemon with an Aegislash in your hand. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Pokemon VMAX.

name: Corviknight V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Sky Hurricane.

name: Corviknight VMAX
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokemon's Abilities done to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use G-Max Hurricane.

name: Spearow
flavorText: Due to its short wings, it can't fly long distances. It wanders about restlessly and pecks at bug Pokemon.

name: Fearow
flavorText: Carrying food through Fearow's territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!

name: Lickitung
flavorText: It licks filth clean with its tongue. Whatever it licks always stinks afterward, so whether it's really clean is…questionable.

name: Lickilicky
flavorText: It uses its tongue much more skillfully than its hands or its feet. It can deftly pick up a single small bean with its tongue.
Attack1Text: Your opponent chooses to discard the top 3 cards of their deck or to discard 3 cards from their hand.
Attack2Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Glameow
flavorText: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

name: Purugly
flavorText: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards. If you do, this Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Stoutland V
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Basic Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, take 1 more Prize card.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Bouffalant
flavorText: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon's attacks do 60 more damage to your opponent's Grass Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Drampa
flavorText: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokemon—up until it's angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Indeedee
flavorText: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 damage for each card in your hand.

name: Rapid Strike Scroll of Swirls
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Single Strike Scroll of Scorn
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Kricketune V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 3 cards in your hand. If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may draw cards until you have 4 cards in your hand instead. You can't use more than 1 Exciting Stage Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Flapple V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon's attacks cost ColorlessColorless more.

name: Victini V
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Empoleon V
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Basic Pokemon in play have no Abilities, except for Pokemon with a Rule Box (Pokemon V, Pokemon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes).
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Empoleon V
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Basic Pokemon in play have no Abilities, except for Pokemon with a Rule Box (Pokemon V, Pokemon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes).
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Tapu Koko V
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Mimikyu V
